caption.p: The cell vitality of the S. cyclophylla 95% aqueous-ethanolic extract. Values denoted are mean ± SEM. The statistical significance was performed via a one-way ANOVA followed by a posthoc test using Tukey’s multi-group comparison: ns: not significant, * p < 0.05, ** p < 0.01, *** p < 0.001, and **** p < 0.0001 compared to fibroblasts. For example, at 50 µg/mL compared to the fibroblasts, the MDA and MCF-7 are not significant, while PANC-1 is significant (** p < 0.01).
